The family 
Nogodinidae
Melichar, 1898 is distributed worldwide in the tropics and subtropics and contains 378 species in 99 genera, including 11 species in Vietnam (
Bourgoin 2023
). Of these 11 species, five were described in the last 10 years (
Constant and Pham 2014
; 
Gnezdilov and Constant 2014
; 
Meng et al. 2014
; 
Constant and Pham 2016
). Within the subfamily 
Nogodininae
Melichar, 1898, the tribe 
Pisachini
Fennah, 1978 was recently reviewed by 
Meng et al. (2014)
and currently counts 10 species in three genera distributed in Southeast Asia (
Constant and Pham 2016
; 
Bourgoin 2023
).

